 (
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
FAIR
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
) the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit in Burt v. Gates
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_Idb76d144279a11f1bc1683b4c14c7e}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_Idb76d144279a11f1bc1683b4c14c7e}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_Idb76d144279a11f1bc1683b4c14" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
54
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 dealt with a suit brought by members of the Yale Law School faculty, who argued that the Supreme Court\rquote s decision in 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
FAIR
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 did not resolve the question of whether the Solomon Amendment,
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_Idb76d145279a11f1bc1683b4c14c7e}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_Idb76d145279a11f1bc1683b4c14c7e}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_Idb76d145279a11f1bc1683b4c14" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
55
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 barring the receipt of federal funds by universities if any part of the university did not allow military recruiters to have access to campus facilities and students on terms equal to those of other employer recruiters, violated the constitutional \u8220\'3facademic freedom\u8221\'3f rights of the faculty members. The Yale faculty members maintained that while the Supreme Court decision in 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
FAIR
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 had clearly held that the Solomon Amendment did not violate any of the free speech or free association rights of law school faculty members or law schools, the law school faculty members nonetheless possessed a distinct constitutional right, the right to \u8220\'3facademic freedom,\u8221\'3f which was not adjudicated in 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
FAIR
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. That distinct academic freedom right, they argued, was violated by the Solomon Amendment. The Second Circuit in Burt v. Gates
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_Idb76d146279a11f1bc1683b4c14c7e}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_Idb76d146279a11f1bc1683b4c14c7e}
