56
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 rejected the argument. The Burt decision is discussed at length later in this Chapter, under the rubric of the question of whether there is a free-standing First Amendment right of \u8220\'3facademic freedom\u8221\'3f that exists separate and apart from recognized First Amendment rights, such as freedom of speech or freedom of association.
}
